6 An Act relating to animals; amending 4 O.S. 2021,
Section 30.8, which relates to animal shelter
7 operators and commercial pet breeders; changing
required notice time to be given to animal shelter
8 operators or commercial pet breeders by the Oklahoma
Department of Agriculture, Food, and Forestry prior
9 to their current license expiring; providing for
online renewals; providing timeline for implementing
10 online renewals; and providing an effective date.
11
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 4 O.S. 2021, Section 30.8, is
15 amended to read as follows:
16 Section 30.8. A. An animal shelter operator or commercial pet
17 breeder who is not in violation of the Commercial Pet Breeders and
18 Animal Shelter Licensing Act or any rule adopted under the
19 Commercial Pet Breeders and Animal Shelter Licensing Act may renew
20 the license of the person by:
21 1. Submitting a renewal application to the Oklahoma Department
22 of Agriculture, Food, and Forestry on the form prescribed by the
23 Department;
24
