1 2. Complying with any other renewal requirements adopted by the
2 Department; and
3 3. Paying the required fee.
4 B. Any person who fails to apply for a renewal in a manner
5 prescribed by the Department, and whose license has expired, may not
6 engage in activities that require a license until the license has
7 been renewed.
8 C. Not later than sixty (60) ninety (90) days before the
9 expiration of the license, the Department shall send written notice
10 of the impending license expiration to the animal shelter operator
11 or commercial pet breeder at the last-known address according to the
12 records of the Department.
13 D. The Department shall provide an online license renewal and
14 payment option by January 1, 2026.
15 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
16 Passed the House of Representatives the 12th day of March, 2025.
